FORD MOTOR COMPANY v. NATIONAL LABOR RELATIONS BOARD. No. 8019. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. Oct. 11, 1939. Frederick H. Wood, William D. Whitney, and Gravath, DeGersdorif, Swaine & Wood, all of New York City, for petitioner. Charles Fahy, of Washington, D. C., for respondent.

Before HICKS and SIMONS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The motion of the National Labor Relations Board to dismiss this cause without prejudice being considered and there having been no objections thereto, it is now ordered and adjudged that this cause be and the same is dismissed without prejudice.
